The paper deals with coded caching schemes in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The construction of optimal PDAs involves combinatorial design theory and hypergraphs, which are topics in computer science (cs.DS). The paper also proposes recursive constructions, which are often used in algorithms and data structures (cs.SI). Finally, the optimization of delivery rate involves minimizing a function, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
